Node Selector
-------------
NodeSelector is a simple scheduling mechanism that places pods on nodes matching specific labels.

NodeSelector is used to run a pod on nodes based on the labels specified on the nodes.

üß† Even simpler (one line)

NodeSelector tells Kubernetes to schedule a pod only on nodes with matching labels.
